cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with causality extraction from natural language texts, which is a problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a neural causality extractor using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of self-attention mechanism and transfer learning also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval from text, which could place it under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
